name: infranea
contents: testnode: custom node for testing, can be used to bugfix problems from other nodes withouth affecting the content of original nodes, Alignment.SetStartEndEndstation: input start and end stations of input alignment, infranea.DynamoClipboard : node used as clipboard for transferring nodes between scripts,  Parameter.SetValueByName : sets element parameter value based on name, Family.CreateNewType : creates new family type in the open family document, material.CreateNew_Uniclass - Creates new materials using 'Cut' settings, 'surface' settings, graphics settings and uniclass coding, based on materialName, Colors.ColorsFromString - formats string to colors, Chart.GetChart - Get chart by type and name, Curve.direction - calculates the direction of curve (cw or ccw) i, based on vector between start and endpoint of curve, Curves.directionbypoints - calculates the direction (cw or ccw) by comparing whether or not the startpoints are equal to previous and same for the endpoints of the curve, Documents.getRoot - Get document rooth w.o. file name based on document, Element.delete_NameContains - Delete alle elements in project by category, where name matches input string, Element.SearchForParameter - searches all element parameter and returns list of matching items, Elements.associateFamParameters - associate family parameters to list of elements, List.ItemsToString - converts list items to string, list to matrix - creates a matrix from (nested) lists, Materials.GetAll - gets all materials of current document, Point.xyz - get xyz coordinates from point, Python.defaultSetupTransaction - Default code for setting up transactions between Dynamo and Revit API, String.isempty - checks if string is an empty string
